      "content": "It sounds like the weight of having \"succeeded\" at everything is making the world feel too quiet to enjoy anymore. Sometimes, the most profound way to find meaning is to let go of the checklist entirely and embrace the gray, even if it feels empty. You are right that the physical journey might be over, but the real one—where you decide what matters most—is happening right now, in this silence.",
