      "content": "it doesn't feel like a journey i can just \"decide\" to continue. it feels more like a flight that's run out of fuel. there's this quietness that comes when you realize there aren't any more departures. it’s almost peaceful, thinking about just... checking out of the terminal. like, if the itinerary is done, why keep staying at the station? why keep waiting for a train that isn't coming?",
